<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-03-1063 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book discusses the induction heating. After reviewing heat treatingoperations for steel and the principles of the heat treatment of steel,an overview of induction heat treating is provided. Next, considerationis given to equipment and equipment selection, coil design, power requirementsand temperature control. A discussion of surface and through hardeningof steel is provided, including information on frequency and power selectionand quenching apparatus. Tempering is considered, followed by informationon control of residual stresses, cracking, temper brittleness and theimportant metallurgical and hardness differences between induction andfurnace treated steel.</TEXT></DOC>